if mibBuilder.loadTexts: aniBsuWirelessPtPConfVerifyAllSu.setDescription("This flag is used to verify if the current set of BSU wireless parameters, that is, aniBsuWirelessPtPConfChannelWidth, aniBsuWirelessPtPConfTargetFrequency, aniBsuWirelessPtPConfBsuId are correctly configured on all the SUs connected. The values are compared against all the SUs connected to this BSU. Sending a Get request on this object causes the agent to verify the above set of parameters. If these set of values are incorrect, an error string is returned indicating that some values are not in sync. If the current set of values are correct, then the string 'No error' is displayed. This object might require upto 10 seconds to respond if multiple SUs are connected. Therefore, to ensure that it does not timeout before getting the complete results, the SNMP Manager tool should increase it's timeout value for this object to more than 10 seconds. ")
